Volume traded on Decentralized Exchanges (DEX) like Uniswap increased 76x t=
o from $2.3 billion in Q1 2020 to $177 billion in Q1 2021.=C2=A0
Total Value Locked, or the amount of ETH staked in DeFi, increased 64x from=
 $800 million to $52 billion.=C2=A0
Beyond finance, NFT art sales increased 562x from $700k to $396 million.=C2=
=A0
Ethereum usage exploded in Q1, and while NFT sales have slowed, partially a=
s a result of high gas fees and partially because the initial euphoria has =
died down, DeFi is still going strong:=C2=A0
Source: DeFi Prime [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEluwzAMRU8T7WpodK=
SFFt30GoIG2hFqS4aGtL59FWdRgCBBfJAf_3nbYM3l1EeuDb2aaecBOsFP3aA1KKhXKCYGTWYqm=
eAKBc0DkUKiWM1SAHYbN91KB3R0t0VvW8zpusCYCvTQnlEnJcWLYncrgErB-H22AivPhBDz29f2=
ECF50PCEcuYEaNOP1o56Y583-jUqwBKPEneYfN6v_ffjmbe-A4qaYkqwoJxQwQWbyEQlOBecd8I=
zzyyhQQlMFfHDMni_3DjeVzrV7mqz_vv1ExWdcnO5xLQO-fthd9guYSQzY-49xXYaSNZtEN6h25=
vdhcGskKAMpsHY9iJG5IwV5nJgu0IOKmye5Z0xhYZzyOMq_Zv-AQq9hUk]
From May 1st through May 22nd, just Uniswap and Sushiswap, the two largest =
Ethereum-based DEXes, handled $78 billion in transaction volume. Q2 will bl=
ow Q1 out of the water.=C2=A0
Despite the explosion in activity and transaction volume, though, the quest=
ion remains: what does that mean for ETH?
How Ethereum Makes Money
I=E2=80=99ve been aware of Ethereum for a long time. I first bought (then s=
old) ETH in 2017, but it was speculative and I didn=E2=80=99t get it. The b=
ig question mark I had with Ethereum was how it made money. How does more a=
ctivity on top of Ethereum translate into a higher price for ETH?
In the near future, the answer will be that more transactions mean higher y=
ields for ETH holders and a decreasing supply of ETH. But that=E2=80=99s no=
t how it works, yet.=C2=A0
Let=E2=80=99s start with how it works today, look at the challenges of the =
current model, the proposed solutions, and what it will look like in the fu=
ture.=C2=A0
(Note: For a more in-depth explanation, listen to Justin Drake on Business =
Breakdowns [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkctq7DAMhp8mXgZfM87Ci0MvdF=
FoFy09nE3wRZ7xNLGD7bSkT1_PzOKAkISE-H8-WV3hmPKu1lQquqSp7iuoCN9lhloho61AnoJTZ=
KCSCT4ip7gjUkgUyuQzwKLDrGreAK2bmYPVNaR4vcCYCnS6VA_MeGuMIwaod95Iay0TgyZEHm66=
enMBogUFX5D3FAHN6lTrWjr2p6OPLdIKsS9rqsHvvU1LG8EaSnLQOvHv78_zw_MH4XLUd-f316f=
z2wvv2GMJHbunjjkvDR4PB8_d6FBQFFOCBeWECi5YT3oqoRk01gjLLNOEulFgOhIrhHDW-o7j5U=
j7splStf28OEBZxVRNyiEe2_rzpBeYr4uGYmp12WKo-wRRmxncjVK9wb5ym44QIbcnuEnXC2IiB=
zxiLhvnK5WGkQ2DPDA2oqbsUruK_0V_AdpnlVA])Today
Today, when you want to transact on Ethereum, you need to use ETH. There ar=
e currently around 116 million ETH, and the price is loosely governed by su=
pply and demand. More transactions on Ethereum means more demand for ETH wh=
ich means higher price, all else equal.=C2=A0
When you transact, say if you send another person ETH, a few things happen:=
=C2=A0
You send 1 ETH and the other person receives 1 ETH
You pay gas fees, say .01 ETH
Your account balance on the chain goes down by 1.01 ETH, theirs goes up by =
1 ETH
To keep Ethereum running, it uses a Proof of Work consensus mechanism [http=
s://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUtuOnDAM_Rp4Kwq5MPDAQ7vd_YK-o-B4hmhCghLTWf=
6-IWy1UuRL4vgc2Qc04SPEY9xCovo0Ex0bjh5fySERxnpPGCdrxrbjvVByqM0oTdurvrZpukfEV=
Vs3Utyx3vbZWdBkgy8_GOOqXkYQvVQakPEWZxCayeEmGUjkZuhlCxeu3o1FDzjiX4xH8Fi7cSHa=
UiV-VvwjH6QFI-5rE-LjTH02Jle7sGFMZxLgdBB8Qp_29GNFWLS3aT2vt_AqfcTZ8PaeLeEnVeL=
3-1ffiiv-dhrm7BNL8MsSBOu_X2CPET25o2R5NrnzG2AkfVWxp_UmlSjci8NMJ6wWSqKJNDxTU_=
HuC_zPYq_yl3XuqnEplGBbdLpohJ2KX623_lHCewyFMPvPvqntyPOImeKy5Uoq0bQN73GezQyzA=
pEn3-aJK8aHFpRSBuBeSbY-eJP2OZ3EGghrHUcfaA7xRJLsuegVXXnI652yX3dv6ZjQ69mhuTZP=
l4CKFqYHeoxZWGbSdMqm7Ts2MNln7ZRNZ2mIrutvQgx1RjYh__LfoP8AWMnW8g] to trustles=
sly agree on the state of the blockchain. Bitcoin also uses Proof of Work, =
that=E2=80=99s where Ethereum got it from, although Bitcoin mining is able =
to be run on cheaper hardware and has 20x more miners than Ethereum, and is=
 therefore more decentralized.
PoW achieves the same thing as your bank account balance going up and someo=
ne else=E2=80=99s going down when they send you money, except in the place =
of a centralized bank, there is a distributed network of miners who agree t=
hat these transactions occurred and that all balances are updated.
To do it, miners around the world race to solve increasingly difficult cryp=
tographic problems in order to create a new block on the blockchain contain=
ing the new transactions. These problems are typically hard to solve -- rea=
d: require a lot of energy -- but easy to verify [https://email.mg2.substac=
k.com/c/eJxFUc3OpCAQfJrhphEQxQOH77KvYfhp1IyCC80a334Z5_AlnabTRacqVVYjLDHd6ow=
ZyafNeJ-gAlx5B0RIpGRI8-YUHZjkop-IU72jUkiy5dkngENvu8JUgJzF7JvVuMXwXHQdE2RVho=
lR-slb3xsY2aC5HsFZw83kpaD0y6uL2yBYUPAP0h0DkF2tiGd-8Z8X-1Pr0LjGCvo9Xm0ArKu_B=
fKHLteZDdMohzpcq8bGxuMs-GjRe3OmaHY4cnPFsrvGQLPE6D7r6JtaV0zv308-psam-8RoS0pA=
NsU6RjvBespEL3hLWybBGGesEZZbrilzk-jYRK0QwlnrX313LKzNxWTU9t1WOSSpENHEtIWlwu9=
VH7A_QPVtru9Rwob3DEFXGe5rKX6TeUyeFwiQamJu1vjJg8qhm7pe1lAeC6vnfBjkyPlEKrOL9S=
r8kv4Hvwip7A]. When a block is entered into the blockchain, the transaction=
s in it officially become part of the record. Miners who successfully creat=
e a block are rewarded with 2 freshly-minted ETH (down from 5 in the beginn=
ing) and all the transaction fees within the block.=C2=A0
Those transaction fees, called gas, are what people pay to submit transacti=
ons to be included in the block. When a user sends someone ETH on Ethereum,=
 or mints an NFT, or does any number of things that need to be validated on=
-chain, they have to pay a gas fee. That gas fee goes towards incentivizing=
 miners to spend the money required, in the form of hardware and electricit=
y, to solve the puzzle and create the block.=C2=A0
So currently, the price of Ethereum is based on a combination of supply and=
 demand, and the price it costs miners to secure the blockchain. To partici=
pate, you need ETH, and you need to pay the gas. Miners receive ETH in the =
form of newly-minted supply and your fees. Miners pay for hardware and elec=
tricity and taxes, and keep ~5% of their earnings. Today, most of the value=
 accrues to GPU makers, electric utilities, and the government, with the mi=
ner=E2=80=99s portion competed down to close to 0.
To learn about how Ethereum makes money, Ultra Sound Money, Legitimacy and =
